{{- if .HasGDPR}}
### GDPR Compliance
This service implements GDPR compliance features:

{{- if .HasGDPRConsent}}
- **Consent Management** (Article 7): Versioned consent records with full audit history
{{- end}}
{{- if .HasGDPRDataExport}}
- **Data Portability** (Article 20): Export all user data in JSON format
{{- end}}
{{- if .HasGDPRDataDeletion}}
- **Right to Erasure** (Article 17): Soft-delete with PII anonymization
{{- end}}
{{- if .HasGDPRProcessingLogs}}
- **Processing Records** (Article 30): Audit trail of all data processing with legal basis
{{- end}}

#### Why Roll Your Own Auth?

The common advice "never roll your own auth" applies to cryptographic primitives, not to building authentication systems using proven libraries. This service:

1. **Uses battle-tested libraries**: bcrypt for password hashing, JWT for tokens, established OAuth libraries
2. **Implements security best practices**: CSRF protection, secure cookies, rate limiting
3. **Provides full control**: You own your data, no vendor lock-in, customizable to your needs
4. **Ensures compliance**: GDPR features are built-in, not bolted on

Third-party auth services may seem easier, but they:
- Create vendor lock-in
- Charge per user (costs scale with success)
- May not meet your data residency requirements
- Limit customization of the auth flow
- Make GDPR compliance your responsibility anyway
{{- end}}
{{- end}}

